<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{9}{y}={36}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}-{7}{y}=-{55}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({9},{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --3. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{3}}{{8}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{3}}}{{8}}{\left({8}{x}+-{9}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{3}}}{{8}}{\left({36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{3}\right)}{x}+-{3.375}{y}={13.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}-{7}{y}=-{55}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10.375}{y}=-{41.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{41.5}}{{-{{10.375}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{9}{\left({4}\right)}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left(-{36}\right)}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={36}-{\left(-{36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{72}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({9},{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

